comment.body:
Thanks for reporting.

> I am guessing that this syntax is wrong sweat_smile

Yes but as a tool for beginners/prototyping Workbench shouldn't crash with cryptic error messages :smile: 

 Unfortunately, the error says it all – it's not possible to preview (or create) `Gtk.Widget` directly because it is an abstract value.

Usually in a UI definition you would use it for a composite template like

```
using Gtk 4.0;
using Adw 1;

template Widget {
    
}
```

Workbench won't crash there (I think I implemented a workaround, but I should do the same for non-template) but it's still not preview-able directly.

I'd recommend extending `Box` or `Button` or whatever instead for now.

issue.body:
From the gjspack readme:
> Support other programming languages? Ping me if there is any interest.

I'd like being able to import `.cljs` (ClojureScript) files and have them executed as javascript.
This can be done by pre-processing the `.cljs` with a ClojureScript compiler or even just https://github.com/squint-cljs/squint.

I was thinking about having a config file similar to
```js
export default {
  importHandlers: {
    "/.*\.blp/": {
      command: "blueprint compile $match",
      generates: "$match.ui",
      importType: "builder",
    }
    "/.*\.cljs/": {
      command: "squint compile $match",
      generates: "$match.js",
      importType: "js",
    },
  }
}
```

Edit: Probably having a custom config file is not the best idea and we should follow the conventions set by webpack, or rollup...

